Text.SourceString: I'm not against ranching. I'm all about coexistence, balance.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not against ranching. I'm all about coexistence, balance.

Text.SourceString: Life on this island, it's always been about respect for all living beings. That's how I want our life together to be...full of respect and love.
Text.LocalizedString: Life on this island, it's always been about respect for all living beings. That's how I want our life together to be...full of respect and love.

Text.SourceString: Working on Dad's ranch has taught me the value of hard work and persistence.
Text.LocalizedString: Working on Dad's ranch has taught me the value of hard work and persistence.

Text.SourceString: I've always felt a deep connection to this place, even before we shared it.
Text.LocalizedString: I've always felt a deep connection to this place, even before we shared it.

Text.SourceString: Are you heading to town, darlin'? If you find some fresh treats, get some for me!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you heading to town, darlin'? If you find some fresh treats, get some for me!

Text.SourceString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=smile>Waking up next to you is a dream.//I feel so lucky to have you by my side.
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=smile>Waking up next to you is a dream.//I feel so lucky to have you by my side.

Text.SourceString: I thought you might be hungry, darlin'.//Here, take this. It's my own recipe.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought you might be hungry, darlin'.//Here, take this. It's my own recipe.

Text.SourceString: I cooked something special for you. It’s my dad's recipe.//I hope it fills your heart as much as it fills your stomach.
Text.LocalizedString: I cooked something special for you. It’s my dad's recipe.//I hope it fills your heart as much as it fills your stomach.

Text.SourceString: I know some of his cooking is questionable, but this one is actually good.
Text.LocalizedString: I know some of his cooking is questionable, but this one is actually good.

Text.SourceString: A rainy day with you feels like a peaceful walk. We should take advantage of it... any ideas?
Text.LocalizedString: A rainy day with you feels like a peaceful walk. We should take advantage of it... any ideas?

Text.SourceString: A rainy day with you feels like a peaceful walk. We should take advantage of it... any ideas?
Text.LocalizedString: A rainy day with you feels like a peaceful walk. We should take advantage of it... any ideas?

Text.SourceString: How was your day? I want to hear all about it.
Text.LocalizedString: How was your day? I want to hear all about it.

Text.SourceString: Living so close to my folks after we got married is kinda neat.//It's like our family just got a bit bigger.
Text.LocalizedString: Living so close to my folks after we got married is kinda neat.//It's like our family just got a bit bigger.

Text.SourceString: The farm, you, me...it's like we're living out a good old country song, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: The farm, you, me...it's like we're living out a good old country song, yeah?

Text.SourceString: You've really got a knack for handling the animals, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You've really got a knack for handling the animals, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I gotta say, <PlayerName>$player</>, the festivals are a whole lot more fun with you by my side.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta say, <PlayerName>$player</>, the festivals are a whole lot more fun with you by my side.

Text.SourceString: I gotta say, <PlayerName>$player</>, the festivals are a whole lot more fun with you by my side.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta say, <PlayerName>$player</>, the festivals are a whole lot more fun with you by my side.

Text.SourceString: I gotta say, <PlayerName>$player</>, the Harvest Festival was  a whole lot more fun with you by my side.
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta say, <PlayerName>$player</>, the Harvest Festival was  a whole lot more fun with you by my side.

Text.SourceString: Who would have thought, <PlayerName>$player</>, a simple rancher like me finding bliss on this tiny island, with you.//It's just...perfect.
Text.LocalizedString: Who would have thought, <PlayerName>$player</>, a simple rancher like me finding bliss on this tiny island, with you.//It's just...perfect.

Text.SourceString: I love you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: You're special to me.
Text.LocalizedString: You're special to me.

Text.SourceString: I love you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: You're special to me.
Text.LocalizedString: You're special to me.

Text.SourceString: I must say, today was a fine one.//<portrait=normal>You'd be surprised what you can find if you just take the time to really look around Dad's ranch.
Text.LocalizedString: I must say, today was a fine one.//<portrait=normal>You'd be surprised what you can find if you just take the time to really look around Dad's ranch.

Text.SourceString: Well, how about you, darlin'? What went down in your world today? Any adventures or discoveries?
Text.LocalizedString: Well, how about you, darlin'? What went down in your world today? Any adventures or discoveries?

Text.SourceString: *Yawn* Reckon I'm nearly ready to hit the hay.
Text.LocalizedString: *Yawn* Reckon I'm nearly ready to hit the hay.

Text.SourceString: You hear that? Night sounds are so much more alive out here.
Text.LocalizedString: You hear that? Night sounds are so much more alive out here.

Text.SourceString: It's music to my ears that never gets old.
Text.LocalizedString: It's music to my ears that never gets old.

Text.SourceString: How about turning in early tonight?
Text.LocalizedString: How about turning in early tonight?

Text.SourceString: Well now, ain't this just the finest mornin'?
Text.LocalizedString: Well now, ain't this just the finest mornin'?

Text.SourceString: Been tendin' to the animals all day.//Mighty fine company they are, though they don't have much to say.
Text.LocalizedString: Been tendin' to the animals all day.//Mighty fine company they are, though they don't have much to say.

Text.SourceString: Nothin' quite like wanderin' back to the homestead after a day at the ranch, greeted by your smile, my darlin'.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothin' quite like wanderin' back to the homestead after a day at the ranch, greeted by your smile, my darlin'.

Text.SourceString: Dad's cookin', bless his heart, might not win any awards, but the man sure puts his all into every dish he whips up.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad's cookin', bless his heart, might not win any awards, but the man sure puts his all into every dish he whips up.

Text.SourceString: I miss them.
Text.LocalizedString: I miss them.

Text.SourceString: Life on the farm ain't never a bore.//From sunrise to sunset, there's always work to be done, animals to tend.
Text.LocalizedString: Life on the farm ain't never a bore.//From sunrise to sunset, there's always work to be done, animals to tend.

Text.SourceString: It's a good kind of tired at the end of the day.
Text.LocalizedString: It's a good kind of tired at the end of the day.

Text.SourceString: I might be out in the woods foragin' today, darlin'.//Nothing beats finding your own supper, makes you appreciate every bite.
Text.LocalizedString: I might be out in the woods foragin' today, darlin'.//Nothing beats finding your own supper, makes you appreciate every bite.

Text.SourceString: What better way to spend a fine Spring day like this than foragin'?
Text.LocalizedString: What better way to spend a fine Spring day like this than foragin'?

Text.SourceString: I'll tell you a secret...a soft melody at twilight, that's the key to a bountiful harvest.//<portrait=daydreaming>Our plants sway to the rhythm, drinking in the notes.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll tell you a secret...a soft melody at twilight, that's the key to a bountiful harvest.//<portrait=daydreaming>Our plants sway to the rhythm, drinking in the notes.

Text.SourceString: You know, I told <NpcName>Theo</> about this. He agreed.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I told <NpcName>Theo</> about this. He agreed.

Text.SourceString: This farm life can be tough, but it's all worth it when I see our crops growin' strong.
Text.LocalizedString: This farm life can be tough, but it's all worth it when I see our crops growin' strong.

Text.SourceString: I swung by Mom's place earlier, and lemme tell you, she won't stop askin' about ya, darlin'.//She sure does adore you.
Text.LocalizedString: I swung by Mom's place earlier, and lemme tell you, she won't stop askin' about ya, darlin'.//She sure does adore you.

Text.SourceString: I'm thinkin' 'bout heading into town later, catch up with my friends.//Need anything while I'm out there'?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm thinkin' 'bout heading into town later, catch up with my friends.//Need anything while I'm out there'?

Text.SourceString: Now don't you overdo it, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//I get to worryin' when you're workin' too hard.
Text.LocalizedString: Now don't you overdo it, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//I get to worryin' when you're workin' too hard.

Text.SourceString: That Mayor, always stirrin' up a storm.//See him dashin' all 'round town, busy as a bee.
Text.LocalizedString: That Mayor, always stirrin' up a storm.//See him dashin' all 'round town, busy as a bee.

Text.SourceString: I ain't much for eggs or milk, stuff like that. But I'm right behind you whatever you choose.
Text.LocalizedString: I ain't much for eggs or milk, stuff like that. But I'm right behind you whatever you choose.

Text.SourceString: Mom always has some guests at the guild, bless her heart.//They make so much noise all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom always has some guests at the guild, bless her heart.//They make so much noise all the time.

Text.SourceString: Just glad I ain't gotta deal with that no more.
Text.LocalizedString: Just glad I ain't gotta deal with that no more.

Text.SourceString: One thing I can tell you, darlin', rancher to rancher.//You need to talk to your animals to connect with them.
Text.LocalizedString: One thing I can tell you, darlin', rancher to rancher.//You need to talk to your animals to connect with them.

Text.SourceString: Animals ain't much different from us.//<portrait=smile>My dad taught me that.
Text.LocalizedString: Animals ain't much different from us.//<portrait=smile>My dad taught me that.

Text.SourceString: Wow. Your life's a hive of activity.//Don't forget to take a breather and commune with Mother Nature.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow. Your life's a hive of activity.//Don't forget to take a breather and commune with Mother Nature.

Text.SourceString: Speak your heart's desires, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>And let nature decide your next steps. That's how I go about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Speak your heart's desires, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>And let nature decide your next steps. That's how I go about it.

Text.SourceString: What a glorious day we're havin'! // I reckon it's gonna be a stellar week.
Text.LocalizedString: What a glorious day we're havin'! // I reckon it's gonna be a stellar week.

Text.SourceString: I just have this feelin' in my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: I just have this feelin' in my bones.

Text.SourceString: No doubt about it, the cows do seem to take kindly to my flute playin'.//It helps 'em wind down a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: No doubt about it, the cows do seem to take kindly to my flute playin'.//It helps 'em wind down a bit.

Text.SourceString: My friends <NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> are very talented blacksmiths.//<portrait=smile>They’re my go-to experts when the ranch needs any tools fixed, bless their hearts.
Text.LocalizedString: My friends <NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> are very talented blacksmiths.//<portrait=smile>They’re my go-to experts when the ranch needs any tools fixed, bless their hearts.

Text.SourceString: The boys make durable weapons too.//Mom always puts in a good word for 'em.
Text.LocalizedString: The boys make durable weapons too.//Mom always puts in a good word for 'em.

Text.SourceString: I don’t carry a weapon or heavy armor around in my bag, only wooden flutes.//Harmless instruments.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t carry a weapon or heavy armor around in my bag, only wooden flutes.//Harmless instruments.

Text.SourceString: And maybe a handful of soybeans.
Text.LocalizedString: And maybe a handful of soybeans.

Text.SourceString: We can grow our own animal feed by growing grass on the farm.//<portrait=normal>It can save us a lot of money.
Text.LocalizedString: We can grow our own animal feed by growing grass on the farm.//<portrait=normal>It can save us a lot of money.

Text.SourceString: But grass doesn’t grow in Winter.//Fact is, most plants don't. So...//<portrait=laugh>That’s when the ranch comes in handy.
Text.LocalizedString: But grass doesn’t grow in Winter.//Fact is, most plants don't. So...//<portrait=laugh>That’s when the ranch comes in handy.

Text.SourceString: I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, no.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, no.

Text.SourceString: No reason. I guess I just don’t have the drive to go to the beach that much.
Text.LocalizedString: No reason. I guess I just don’t have the drive to go to the beach that much.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I might go to Fishensips this weekend.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I might go to Fishensips this weekend.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever looked at the sky and wondered what’s out there?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever looked at the sky and wondered what’s out there?

Text.SourceString: I spend a lot of my free time doing just that.//<portrait=daydreaming>Looking at the sky, letting my mind wander.//<portrait=normal>This world sometimes feels too small for my imagination.
Text.LocalizedString: I spend a lot of my free time doing just that.//<portrait=daydreaming>Looking at the sky, letting my mind wander.//<portrait=normal>This world sometimes feels too small for my imagination.

Text.SourceString: I learned this from my granddad.//So, once you have animals, make sure to talk to them every day. It’s all they need.//<portrait=concerned>And food. You get that, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I learned this from my granddad.//So, once you have animals, make sure to talk to them every day. It’s all they need.//<portrait=concerned>And food. You get that, right?

Text.SourceString: Don’t forget to feed them, of course!//<portrait=normal>I hope that one is obvious.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t forget to feed them, of course!//<portrait=normal>I hope that one is obvious.

Text.SourceString: Make sure to keep your animals inside when it rains, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to keep your animals inside when it rains, yeah?

Text.SourceString: I have no worries when I’m around you. You're a loving person, darlin'.//<portrait=normal>You just have that aura.
Text.LocalizedString: I have no worries when I’m around you. You're a loving person, darlin'.//<portrait=normal>You just have that aura.

Text.SourceString: Kombucha is the best drink to have with lunch. Love it, yeah?//Especially when it’s sunny out. It has that refreshing kick, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Kombucha is the best drink to have with lunch. Love it, yeah?//Especially when it’s sunny out. It has that refreshing kick, you know?

Text.SourceString: I prefer to have my lunch break outdoors. Be one with nature, yeah? 'Course, that's when the weather's agreeable.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to have my lunch break outdoors. Be one with nature, yeah? 'Course, that's when the weather's agreeable.

Text.SourceString: Hmm... Times when my words don't quite cut it, I lean on my flute to do the speakin'.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm... Times when my words don't quite cut it, I lean on my flute to do the speakin'.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, well... there just ain't no other way 'round it. Words alone just ain't enough.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, well... there just ain't no other way 'round it. Words alone just ain't enough.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a fan of processed foods.//I read in some place they're cooked up to make us hooked on 'em.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a fan of processed foods.//I read in some place they're cooked up to make us hooked on 'em.

Text.SourceString: Ain't that a fright?
Text.LocalizedString: Ain't that a fright?

Text.SourceString: The more I think about us, folks, the sadder I get. We put chemicals in our food.//Some of us, we push others around for no good reason. Just ain't right.
Text.LocalizedString: The more I think about us, folks, the sadder I get. We put chemicals in our food.//Some of us, we push others around for no good reason. Just ain't right.

Text.SourceString: *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: *sighs*

Text.SourceString: I don’t like processed foods, but I’m not gonna lie, I eat 'em  once in a while.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like processed foods, but I’m not gonna lie, I eat 'em  once in a while.

Text.SourceString: I just get really sleepy afterward. Ain't a great feeling, not one bit. Blech!
Text.LocalizedString: I just get really sleepy afterward. Ain't a great feeling, not one bit. Blech!

Text.SourceString: Wild fruit and mushrooms are gifts of nature.//They’re so easy to find around here.
Text.LocalizedString: Wild fruit and mushrooms are gifts of nature.//They’re so easy to find around here.

Text.SourceString: Mom used to slay monsters for a living, but she's hung up her sword for now.//<portrait=normal>Reckons the island's peaceful enough these days, so she just keeps an eye on that cavern.//Wouldn't let me nowhere near that place as a kid. Monster infested, she said.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom used to slay monsters for a living, but she's hung up her sword for now.//<portrait=normal>Reckons the island's peaceful enough these days, so she just keeps an eye on that cavern.//Wouldn't let me nowhere near that place as a kid. Monster infested, she said.

Text.SourceString: My folks and I... We don't always see eye-to-eye on everything, but they respect my views, and that means a lot.//<portrait=normal>For example, my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, but they don’t force that view on me. I celebrate mine, all right!//Born and bred in Spring, on the 9th!
Text.LocalizedString: My folks and I... We don't always see eye-to-eye on everything, but they respect my views, and that means a lot.//<portrait=normal>For example, my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, but they don’t force that view on me. I celebrate mine, all right!//Born and bred in Spring, on the 9th!

Text.SourceString: Another year has begun. These cherry blossoms are a beautiful reminder.
Text.LocalizedString: Another year has begun. These cherry blossoms are a beautiful reminder.

Text.SourceString: Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.

Text.SourceString: Spring is my favorite time of year!//<portrait=normal>The flowers are opening up, the fawns are learning to walk. It feels like everything is waking up after Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is my favorite time of year!//<portrait=normal>The flowers are opening up, the fawns are learning to walk. It feels like everything is waking up after Winter.

Text.SourceString: Havin' my birthday in Spring, now that's a blessing.//<portrait=daydreaming>It feels like nature is putting on a show for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Havin' my birthday in Spring, now that's a blessing.//<portrait=daydreaming>It feels like nature is putting on a show for me.

Text.SourceString: Even if I weren’t here, the natural world would keep on going without me.//<portrait=normal>Sounds a bit gloomy, I know, but there's a certain comfort in it for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Even if I weren’t here, the natural world would keep on going without me.//<portrait=normal>Sounds a bit gloomy, I know, but there's a certain comfort in it for me.

Text.SourceString: There are so many delicious things you can grow in Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>My mouth is watering with all the taco possibilities…
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many delicious things you can grow in Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>My mouth is watering with all the taco possibilities…

Text.SourceString: Spring is the time to plan for the year to come.//Have you taken stock of all your crops and animals yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is the time to plan for the year to come.//Have you taken stock of all your crops and animals yet?

Text.SourceString: Good sense to keep things organized, mind you.
Text.LocalizedString: Good sense to keep things organized, mind you.

Text.SourceString: Can you hear it, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The trees, they're singin'. Buzzin' with joy that Spring's here at last.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you hear it, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The trees, they're singin'. Buzzin' with joy that Spring's here at last.

Text.SourceString: I’m playing along with the trees, <PlayerName>$player</>. Happy as can be.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m playing along with the trees, <PlayerName>$player</>. Happy as can be.

Text.SourceString: Hey, you wanna join me and listen to the birds? They’re so cheerful right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, you wanna join me and listen to the birds? They’re so cheerful right now.

Text.SourceString: Nothin' like being able to have your lunch out in the open again.//I missed doing that in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothin' like being able to have your lunch out in the open again.//I missed doing that in Winter.

Text.SourceString: Why coop up indoors when there's all this beauty outside? Just look at all these blossoms!
Text.LocalizedString: Why coop up indoors when there's all this beauty outside? Just look at all these blossoms!

Text.SourceString: Finally, Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>I welcome the sound of the creatures coming back to life.
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>I welcome the sound of the creatures coming back to life.

Text.SourceString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>! The birds are makin' their way back, one by one.//Ain't their songs just the sweetest thing?
Text.LocalizedString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>! The birds are makin' their way back, one by one.//Ain't their songs just the sweetest thing?

Text.SourceString: I think the daisies in Summer are nature telling us it’s happy and healthy. Don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: I think the daisies in Summer are nature telling us it’s happy and healthy. Don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: Since the days are longer in Summer, it’s nice to have all this time to spend outside.
Text.LocalizedString: Since the days are longer in Summer, it’s nice to have all this time to spend outside.

Text.SourceString: It’s hotter than I’d like for eating outside, but it’s much better than eating inside.//<portrait=daydreaming>Nothing beats eating in nature, not even air-conditioned rooms.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hotter than I’d like for eating outside, but it’s much better than eating inside.//<portrait=daydreaming>Nothing beats eating in nature, not even air-conditioned rooms.

Text.SourceString: Sure, the Summer heat makes my work harder, but I’d rather sweat it out surrounded by nature than stay inside.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, the Summer heat makes my work harder, but I’d rather sweat it out surrounded by nature than stay inside.

Text.SourceString: I’m a little sad, darlin'. The trees are starting to lose their leaves, and the animals are leaving.//<portrait=normal>Well, at least I've still got the ranch animals for company.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a little sad, darlin'. The trees are starting to lose their leaves, and the animals are leaving.//<portrait=normal>Well, at least I've still got the ranch animals for company.

Text.SourceString: I’m savoring all the time I can spend outside now.//<portrait=sad>In about a week, I won’t be able to enjoy the outdoors like this.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m savoring all the time I can spend outside now.//<portrait=sad>In about a week, I won’t be able to enjoy the outdoors like this.

Text.SourceString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=concerned>A lot of birds are migrating south.//Goodbye, sweet birds.//<portrait=daydreaming>I’ll see you again in Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=concerned>A lot of birds are migrating south.//Goodbye, sweet birds.//<portrait=daydreaming>I’ll see you again in Spring.

Text.SourceString: Want some of my green tea, <PlayerName>$player</>? I always carry some in Fall. It’s a nice, quick warm-up when it’s chilly.
Text.LocalizedString: Want some of my green tea, <PlayerName>$player</>? I always carry some in Fall. It’s a nice, quick warm-up when it’s chilly.

Text.SourceString: Not gonna lie, Winter bums me out a bit. The trees are quiet, and a lot of animals are either hibernating or have migrated to somewhere warmer.
Text.LocalizedString: Not gonna lie, Winter bums me out a bit. The trees are quiet, and a lot of animals are either hibernating or have migrated to somewhere warmer.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a big fan of the cold.//It’s hard to eat your lunch outside when you’re constantly shivering.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a big fan of the cold.//It’s hard to eat your lunch outside when you’re constantly shivering.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could hibernate like the bears. Sleep through the cold Winter and wake up when it’s warm again in Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could hibernate like the bears. Sleep through the cold Winter and wake up when it’s warm again in Spring.

Text.SourceString: When it’s cold like this, there’s nothing like a cup of hot green tea to warm you up.
Text.LocalizedString: When it’s cold like this, there’s nothing like a cup of hot green tea to warm you up.

Text.SourceString: Winter makes me think of roasted almonds.//<portrait=normal>Hmm, maybe I’ll stop by Sam’s and buy some to roast over the fire.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter makes me think of roasted almonds.//<portrait=normal>Hmm, maybe I’ll stop by Sam’s and buy some to roast over the fire.

Text.SourceString: Winter is always so quiet.//Hear that? Basically nothing. Just faint music far, <Italic>far</> away.//Don’t worry, I hear it too. It’s nature’s music.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is always so quiet.//Hear that? Basically nothing. Just faint music far, <Italic>far</> away.//Don’t worry, I hear it too. It’s nature’s music.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait to hear the birds again, <PlayerName>$player</>. I miss their songs on my morning walks.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to hear the birds again, <PlayerName>$player</>. I miss their songs on my morning walks.

Text.SourceString: It’s so cold that even a hot cup of green tea isn’t helping.//<portrait=sad>I should just head inside.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so cold that even a hot cup of green tea isn’t helping.//<portrait=sad>I should just head inside.

Text.SourceString: The hot spring sounds so good right now.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot spring sounds so good right now.

Text.SourceString: The bugs are always thickest in Summer.//Just yesterday, found a wasp in the barn, took it outside.
Text.LocalizedString: The bugs are always thickest in Summer.//Just yesterday, found a wasp in the barn, took it outside.

Text.SourceString: It stung me, but I think it was just scared.
Text.LocalizedString: It stung me, but I think it was just scared.

Text.SourceString: The color of the lake is so beautiful this time of year.//When you splash, the water catches the sunlight, makin' tiny rainbows.
Text.LocalizedString: The color of the lake is so beautiful this time of year.//When you splash, the water catches the sunlight, makin' tiny rainbows.

Text.SourceString: Let’s go swimming there sometime!
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s go swimming there sometime!

Text.SourceString: You harvested any pineapples yet?//Heard they're somethin' special when grilled!
Text.LocalizedString: You harvested any pineapples yet?//Heard they're somethin' special when grilled!

Text.SourceString: Summer heat makes moving the animals twice as hard. It’s not so bad, though.//At least it’s already light when I get up in the morning!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer heat makes moving the animals twice as hard. It’s not so bad, though.//At least it’s already light when I get up in the morning!

Text.SourceString: But you sure wouldn't wanna be anywhere near me after work, phew!
Text.LocalizedString: But you sure wouldn't wanna be anywhere near me after work, phew!

Text.SourceString: Oopsie! Got a bit of pollen on my hat.//Lucky it didn't fall in my eyes.
Text.LocalizedString: Oopsie! Got a bit of pollen on my hat.//Lucky it didn't fall in my eyes.

Text.SourceString: Is there a flower nearby that I can brush it on?
Text.LocalizedString: Is there a flower nearby that I can brush it on?

Text.SourceString: Incredible how time flies, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Incredible how time flies, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I was shocked to wake up this morning and realize it’s already the 17th. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: I was shocked to wake up this morning and realize it’s already the 17th. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is zoning out.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is zoning out.]

Text.SourceString: Funbucket, bless his little feathered heart, is one of our ducks.//But <NPCName>Ben</> comes by often to help out with the animals, and they seem to have bonded. So now, Funbucket is his duck too.
Text.LocalizedString: Funbucket, bless his little feathered heart, is one of our ducks.//But <NPCName>Ben</> comes by often to help out with the animals, and they seem to have bonded. So now, Funbucket is his duck too.

Text.SourceString: This is the most beautiful foliage I’ve ever seen on Coral Island!
Text.LocalizedString: This is the most beautiful foliage I’ve ever seen on Coral Island!

Text.SourceString: I reckon I say that every year, but this time I mean it!
Text.LocalizedString: I reckon I say that every year, but this time I mean it!

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to catch as much sun as I can by the lake while it’s still Fall.//Once Winter comes, the sun is too weak to warm you up.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to catch as much sun as I can by the lake while it’s still Fall.//Once Winter comes, the sun is too weak to warm you up.

Text.SourceString: I guess that’s what Fishensips is good for. Nothing warms you up like a hot tea on a chilly evening!
Text.LocalizedString: I guess that’s what Fishensips is good for. Nothing warms you up like a hot tea on a chilly evening!

Text.SourceString: Fall is the most delicious time of year! Nothing beats harvest time for a good meal…or five.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is the most delicious time of year! Nothing beats harvest time for a good meal…or five.

Text.SourceString: Hmm... What was I thinkin' 'bout again?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm... What was I thinkin' 'bout again?

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Sorry, I just got a little lost in the color of the trees.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Sorry, I just got a little lost in the color of the trees.

Text.SourceString: This island looks like a whole new place when it's covered in snow like this.
Text.LocalizedString: This island looks like a whole new place when it's covered in snow like this.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is zoning out.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is zoning out.]

Text.SourceString: My old man enters a cookin' competition every darn year.//Mom and I usually go to town to watch and give him emotional support.
Text.LocalizedString: My old man enters a cookin' competition every darn year.//Mom and I usually go to town to watch and give him emotional support.

Text.SourceString: He likes things like that.
Text.LocalizedString: He likes things like that.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad we have a heater for the animals at the ranch.//<portrait=concerned>I hate to think about them being cold and lonely when I’m not there.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad we have a heater for the animals at the ranch.//<portrait=concerned>I hate to think about them being cold and lonely when I’m not there.

Text.SourceString: Make sure you stay bundled up, <PlayerName>$player</>. Even though we’re on an island, it can get pretty chilly.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure you stay bundled up, <PlayerName>$player</>. Even though we’re on an island, it can get pretty chilly.

Text.SourceString: The plants and animals are all sleeping, tucked away under the snow. It makes me feel like I should be sleeping too.
Text.LocalizedString: The plants and animals are all sleeping, tucked away under the snow. It makes me feel like I should be sleeping too.

Text.SourceString: I guess I’ve always known I wanted to work with animals.//I want to make sure they’re properly cared for.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I’ve always known I wanted to work with animals.//I want to make sure they’re properly cared for.

Text.SourceString: Our animals don’t like the rain very much.//<NPCName>Luke</> said Taco hates it too.//<portrait=laugh>He gets really lazy and stays inside the house all day when it rains.
Text.LocalizedString: Our animals don’t like the rain very much.//<NPCName>Luke</> said Taco hates it too.//<portrait=laugh>He gets really lazy and stays inside the house all day when it rains.

Text.SourceString: I guess I’ve always known I wanted to work with animals.//I want to make sure they’re properly cared for.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I’ve always known I wanted to work with animals.//I want to make sure they’re properly cared for.

Text.SourceString: Keep warm, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep warm, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Have you checked on your animals today?//<portrait=smile>They could use extra love on days like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you checked on your animals today?//<portrait=smile>They could use extra love on days like this.

Text.SourceString: Animals get cold too, especially when it’s snowing like this. Make sure to turn your heater on, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Animals get cold too, especially when it’s snowing like this. Make sure to turn your heater on, okay?

Text.SourceString: To keep warm during Winter, Mom used to go to the cavern and slay monsters.//<portrait=concerned>I felt kind of bad for her.
Text.LocalizedString: To keep warm during Winter, Mom used to go to the cavern and slay monsters.//<portrait=concerned>I felt kind of bad for her.

Text.SourceString: I’m curious to see how beautiful the view must be from up above.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m curious to see how beautiful the view must be from up above.

Text.SourceString: I can imagine watching the snow as it falls.
Text.LocalizedString: I can imagine watching the snow as it falls.

Text.SourceString: My old man taught me how to handle animals at a young age.//I feel like almost all my significant memories are here on this ranch.
Text.LocalizedString: My old man taught me how to handle animals at a young age.//I feel like almost all my significant memories are here on this ranch.

Text.SourceString: The loudest quack is Funbucket’s.//<portrait=smile>He's our most outspoken duck, no doubt about it.
Text.LocalizedString: The loudest quack is Funbucket’s.//<portrait=smile>He's our most outspoken duck, no doubt about it.

Text.SourceString: We could use an extra heater here.//<portrait=normal>Can I help you with anything?
Text.LocalizedString: We could use an extra heater here.//<portrait=normal>Can I help you with anything?

Text.SourceString: While you're here, lemme just say somethin' real quick.//You still need to feed your animals, even though they’re out during the day.
Text.LocalizedString: While you're here, lemme just say somethin' real quick.//You still need to feed your animals, even though they’re out during the day.

Text.SourceString: Just thought I’d pay the <NPCName>Sanchez</> brothers a visit.//It’s been a while since we all hung out.
Text.LocalizedString: Just thought I’d pay the <NPCName>Sanchez</> brothers a visit.//It’s been a while since we all hung out.

Text.SourceString: I’m not going to buy anything today.//It’s probably not the wisest choice to carry around electronics in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not going to buy anything today.//It’s probably not the wisest choice to carry around electronics in this weather.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… What do you think that painting over there is trying to say?//It's got me curious.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… What do you think that painting over there is trying to say?//It's got me curious.

Text.SourceString: So many thoughts went into that art piece.//<portrait=daydreaming>When I look at it, I can feel conviction and hope deep down in my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: So many thoughts went into that art piece.//<portrait=daydreaming>When I look at it, I can feel conviction and hope deep down in my bones.

Text.SourceString: It's good to be back here.
Text.LocalizedString: It's good to be back here.

Text.SourceString: A bit too stuffy in here at the moment.//<portrait=concerned>I think the humidity is getting to us.
Text.LocalizedString: A bit too stuffy in here at the moment.//<portrait=concerned>I think the humidity is getting to us.

Text.SourceString: Please help yourself, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>We’re all family here.
Text.LocalizedString: Please help yourself, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>We’re all family here.

Text.SourceString: Lunch tastes so much better here, ain't it?
Text.LocalizedString: Lunch tastes so much better here, ain't it?

Text.SourceString: I remember Mom brought some weird things home from her combat excursions.//<portrait=smile>My treasure chest was full of silver spoons and colorful rocks.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember Mom brought some weird things home from her combat excursions.//<portrait=smile>My treasure chest was full of silver spoons and colorful rocks.

Text.SourceString: I prefer to spend my time in nature.//<portrait=daydreaming>Here and the forest are two of my favorite places.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to spend my time in nature.//<portrait=daydreaming>Here and the forest are two of my favorite places.

Text.SourceString: Just smell that fresh air!//<portrait=smile>I’m so lucky I get to work outside.
Text.LocalizedString: Just smell that fresh air!//<portrait=smile>I’m so lucky I get to work outside.

Text.SourceString: This might sound weird, but I don’t mind the smell of manure.//Dad was telling me it makes great fertilizer for the fields!
Text.LocalizedString: This might sound weird, but I don’t mind the smell of manure.//Dad was telling me it makes great fertilizer for the fields!

Text.SourceString: Is that gross?//Sorry. I just think it’s cool that even animal waste has a good use.
Text.LocalizedString: Is that gross?//Sorry. I just think it’s cool that even animal waste has a good use.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, have you fed your animals yet today? They could get sick if you forget to feed them.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, have you fed your animals yet today? They could get sick if you forget to feed them.

Text.SourceString: Whoops! I almost bumped into you!//<portrait=normal>Where are you off to in such a rush?
Text.LocalizedString: Whoops! I almost bumped into you!//<portrait=normal>Where are you off to in such a rush?

Text.SourceString: Make sure you take time to smell the roses! And the petunias, and the tulips, and the daisies…
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure you take time to smell the roses! And the petunias, and the tulips, and the daisies…

Text.SourceString: What’s that amazing smell? Did you bring me a snack, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s that amazing smell? Did you bring me a snack, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I took one of my tools to <NPCName>Rafael</> to repair. It came back good as new!
Text.LocalizedString: I took one of my tools to <NPCName>Rafael</> to repair. It came back good as new!

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, Bessie won’t step on it again.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, Bessie won’t step on it again.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been trying to learn this new song on my flute, but it’s not going so well.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been trying to learn this new song on my flute, but it’s not going so well.

Text.SourceString: I better check that there weather forecast for tomorrow.//We’ll have to put the animals in the barn if it rains.
Text.LocalizedString: I better check that there weather forecast for tomorrow.//We’ll have to put the animals in the barn if it rains.

Text.SourceString: It’s Friday! I can’t wait to celebrate at the Tavern tonight.//<portrait=normal>Come with me?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Friday! I can’t wait to celebrate at the Tavern tonight.//<portrait=normal>Come with me?

Text.SourceString: Well now, I gotta work tomorrow mornin' myself, but any excuse to spend time with <NPCName>Frank</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> is a good one.//Can't beat good company, I reckon.
Text.LocalizedString: Well now, I gotta work tomorrow mornin' myself, but any excuse to spend time with <NPCName>Frank</> and <NPCName>Pablo</> is a good one.//Can't beat good company, I reckon.

Text.SourceString: The mayor was telling me the other day that you’re quite the rancher!//<portrait=normal>So proud of you, darlin'.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor was telling me the other day that you’re quite the rancher!//<portrait=normal>So proud of you, darlin'.

Text.SourceString: When you work with animals like I do, you start to hear moos and baas in your sleep.
Text.LocalizedString: When you work with animals like I do, you start to hear moos and baas in your sleep.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I even hear them when I zone out.//<portrait=laugh>Or maybe that’s because there’s a cow standing right behind me.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I even hear them when I zone out.//<portrait=laugh>Or maybe that’s because there’s a cow standing right behind me.

Text.SourceString: Animals that are taken care of well give the best milk, wool, and eggs.//The money from the sale of that stuff helps the businesses around here.
Text.LocalizedString: Animals that are taken care of well give the best milk, wool, and eggs.//The money from the sale of that stuff helps the businesses around here.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, money is nice.//<portrait=concerned>But it shouldn’t be the only reason to be kind to animals.//<portrait=normal>They deserve love, just like we do.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, money is nice.//<portrait=concerned>But it shouldn’t be the only reason to be kind to animals.//<portrait=normal>They deserve love, just like we do.

Text.SourceString: Animals are fine listeners.//Even though they don't have a way of talking back to us, I always feel like they're taking in every word I say.
Text.LocalizedString: Animals are fine listeners.//Even though they don't have a way of talking back to us, I always feel like they're taking in every word I say.

Text.SourceString: Or maybe they’re just waiting to see if I pull a snack out of my pocket.//<portrait=smile>That’s also possible.
Text.LocalizedString: Or maybe they’re just waiting to see if I pull a snack out of my pocket.//<portrait=smile>That’s also possible.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, whoa! Be careful!//<portrait=concerned>You almost stepped on that ant.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, whoa! Be careful!//<portrait=concerned>You almost stepped on that ant.

Text.SourceString: I lent my best tool to <NPCName>Ben</>, but he hasn’t given it back yet. Should I ask him about it?
Text.LocalizedString: I lent my best tool to <NPCName>Ben</>, but he hasn’t given it back yet. Should I ask him about it?

Text.SourceString: Oh well. He’ll probably return it when he’s done.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well. He’ll probably return it when he’s done.

Text.SourceString: I always bring extra food for the ants when I come here.
Text.LocalizedString: I always bring extra food for the ants when I come here.

Text.SourceString: Wow, it’s been raining since this morning.//<portrait=sad>The animals aren’t going to be happy about being cooped up all day.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow, it’s been raining since this morning.//<portrait=sad>The animals aren’t going to be happy about being cooped up all day.

Text.SourceString: I hope it clears up tomorrow. I really want to eat in the forest again.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it clears up tomorrow. I really want to eat in the forest again.

Text.SourceString: There’s not much you can do outside when it’s raining, so I like to pass the time in here.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s not much you can do outside when it’s raining, so I like to pass the time in here.

Text.SourceString: As amazing as watching nature is, I’d rather not be soaking wet while I do it.
Text.LocalizedString: As amazing as watching nature is, I’d rather not be soaking wet while I do it.

Text.SourceString: I guess leaving animals out in the rain might make 'em cleaner, but it also gets 'em mighty upset.//<portrait=normal>You should always be sure your animals have a dry place to stay when it rains.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess leaving animals out in the rain might make 'em cleaner, but it also gets 'em mighty upset.//<portrait=normal>You should always be sure your animals have a dry place to stay when it rains.

Text.SourceString: I sleep so well when it’s raining.//<portrait=daydreaming>The <Italic>tap tap tap</> on my window is strangely comforting.
Text.LocalizedString: I sleep so well when it’s raining.//<portrait=daydreaming>The <Italic>tap tap tap</> on my window is strangely comforting.

Text.SourceString: This storm is really nasty, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=concerned>You shouldn’t be out in it!
Text.LocalizedString: This storm is really nasty, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=concerned>You shouldn’t be out in it!

Text.SourceString: I really shouldn’t be out here in weather like this, but I couldn’t help myself.//<portrait=smile>I wanted to see nature’s power firsthand!
Text.LocalizedString: I really shouldn’t be out here in weather like this, but I couldn’t help myself.//<portrait=smile>I wanted to see nature’s power firsthand!

Text.SourceString: To be safe inside, with a roof over my head during a storm… It makes me feel very grateful.
Text.LocalizedString: To be safe inside, with a roof over my head during a storm… It makes me feel very grateful.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Just look at her go…
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Just look at her go…

Text.SourceString: Oh! My apologies there.//<portrait=normal>I sort of got lost in the swirling wind.//<portrait=laugh>It's all very theatrical, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! My apologies there.//<portrait=normal>I sort of got lost in the swirling wind.//<portrait=laugh>It's all very theatrical, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: Snow is part of nature, but it’s not my favorite part.//<portrait=laugh>I’d rather be stretched out under the Spring sun than slipping on this ice.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow is part of nature, but it’s not my favorite part.//<portrait=laugh>I’d rather be stretched out under the Spring sun than slipping on this ice.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I’m not out there working in that slush.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t like it, the animals don’t like it. It’s a bad time all around.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I’m not out there working in that slush.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t like it, the animals don’t like it. It’s a bad time all around.

Text.SourceString: I hope this snow stops tomorrow.//Maybe I can go digging for root vegetables after work.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this snow stops tomorrow.//Maybe I can go digging for root vegetables after work.

Text.SourceString: *shivering* Someone light a fire! I’m freezing in here!
Text.LocalizedString: *shivering* Someone light a fire! I’m freezing in here!

Text.SourceString: Got a blanket on you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=concerned>No?//<portrait=normal>Well, that's alright then.
Text.LocalizedString: Got a blanket on you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=concerned>No?//<portrait=normal>Well, that's alright then.

Text.SourceString: Is it just me, or does snow make Winter nights twice as cold?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it just me, or does snow make Winter nights twice as cold?

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>! Watch where you step.//<portrait=normal>You never know where you’ll find manure!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>! Watch where you step.//<portrait=normal>You never know where you’ll find manure!

Text.SourceString: Have you ever looked into an animal’s eyes and wondered what they’re thinking or what they’d say if they could talk?//<portrait=daydreaming>It’s one of my favorite things to think about.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever looked into an animal’s eyes and wondered what they’re thinking or what they’d say if they could talk?//<portrait=daydreaming>It’s one of my favorite things to think about.

Text.SourceString: Building a relationship is like growing a flower. It should happen organically.//You can’t force it. Relationships are fragile and beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: Building a relationship is like growing a flower. It should happen organically.//You can’t force it. Relationships are fragile and beautiful.

Text.SourceString: Some relationships aren’t meant to last long. They wilt when it’s time.//Remember to enjoy it while it’s in bloom.
Text.LocalizedString: Some relationships aren’t meant to last long. They wilt when it’s time.//Remember to enjoy it while it’s in bloom.

Text.SourceString: That’s a nice Summer outfit you got, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//I should get something like that. What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: That’s a nice Summer outfit you got, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//I should get something like that. What do you think?

Text.SourceString: I learned how to play pool from <NpcName>Pablo</>. Taught me everything I know.//<portrait=happy>That man is a legend.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned how to play pool from <NpcName>Pablo</>. Taught me everything I know.//<portrait=happy>That man is a legend.

Text.SourceString: Drink on me, cutie?
Text.LocalizedString: Drink on me, cutie?

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: I went into the cavern last week and got attacked by giant lava spiders! Phew.//I must’ve spooked them.
Text.LocalizedString: I went into the cavern last week and got attacked by giant lava spiders! Phew.//I must’ve spooked them.

Text.SourceString: I almost passed out trying to get them off me!
Text.LocalizedString: I almost passed out trying to get them off me!

Text.SourceString: I don’t like carrying weapons.//If I’m attacked, then I’m attacked. It’s all right.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like carrying weapons.//If I’m attacked, then I’m attacked. It’s all right.

Text.SourceString: Fall is giving you a magnificent glow today.//<portrait=blushing>I hope your day so far has been as good as you look.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is giving you a magnificent glow today.//<portrait=blushing>I hope your day so far has been as good as you look.

Text.SourceString: Going on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Going on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Going for a dip, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Going for a dip, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I– Oh no, I stepped on a worm!
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I– Oh no, I stepped on a worm!

Text.SourceString: I feel horrible.//<portrait=concerned>Will you help me bury it? No animal deserves to be stepped on, even the littlest ones.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel horrible.//<portrait=concerned>Will you help me bury it? No animal deserves to be stepped on, even the littlest ones.

Text.SourceString: I might go to Sam’s later. Do you need anything?//I can pick you up some flour or… What do you need?
Text.LocalizedString: I might go to Sam’s later. Do you need anything?//I can pick you up some flour or… What do you need?

Text.SourceString: I like this place. Nice and cold inside.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this place. Nice and cold inside.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Luke</> has an electric flute here.//I was thinking of getting it, but I don’t think I’d be disciplined enough to recharge the battery.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Luke</> has an electric flute here.//I was thinking of getting it, but I don’t think I’d be disciplined enough to recharge the battery.

Text.SourceString: I just can’t get this song right.//<portrait=sad>I’ve been working on it for weeks, but it’s not going well.
Text.LocalizedString: I just can’t get this song right.//<portrait=sad>I’ve been working on it for weeks, but it’s not going well.

Text.SourceString: You want to help me? That’s kind of you.//<portrait=normal>It’s, uh, something I have to do on my own, though. Unless you can read my mind. Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: You want to help me? That’s kind of you.//<portrait=normal>It’s, uh, something I have to do on my own, though. Unless you can read my mind. Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: Some of these trees have been here for a hundred years or more.//They’ll probably be here a hundred years after you and I are gone, too.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of these trees have been here for a hundred years or more.//They’ll probably be here a hundred years after you and I are gone, too.

Text.SourceString: That might sound depressing, but I think it’s pretty romantic, actually.//<portrait=daydreaming>Old trees, the sentinels of the forest. It’s like something out of a fairy tale.
Text.LocalizedString: That might sound depressing, but I think it’s pretty romantic, actually.//<portrait=daydreaming>Old trees, the sentinels of the forest. It’s like something out of a fairy tale.

Text.SourceString: What’s your favorite drink? Mine’s green tea.//<NpcName>Frank</> here can whip up just about any drink ya fancy. He's quite the master behind that bar.
Text.LocalizedString: What’s your favorite drink? Mine’s green tea.//<NpcName>Frank</> here can whip up just about any drink ya fancy. He's quite the master behind that bar.

Text.SourceString: Kombucha is great too. But I don’t think they sell any here.
Text.LocalizedString: Kombucha is great too. But I don’t think they sell any here.

Text.SourceString: I just had my dinner, and I’m <Italic>starving</>. What’s good here?
Text.LocalizedString: I just had my dinner, and I’m <Italic>starving</>. What’s good here?

Text.SourceString: Well, ain't this a nice way to end the day, takin' a moment to relax and unwind.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, ain't this a nice way to end the day, takin' a moment to relax and unwind.

Text.SourceString: I ran into <NpcName>Joko</> a couple of times by the creek near Ben’s caravan. He seems to like fishing there.//Oh, I was on my way to the hot spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into <NpcName>Joko</> a couple of times by the creek near Ben’s caravan. He seems to like fishing there.//Oh, I was on my way to the hot spring.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Joko</> takes his son fishing with him.//Reminds me of my own childhood with my old man.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Joko</> takes his son fishing with him.//Reminds me of my own childhood with my old man.

Text.SourceString: Where do people go in Summer? It seems like it’s not as lively out right now.//<portrait=happy>Ah, right. They’re probably at the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: Where do people go in Summer? It seems like it’s not as lively out right now.//<portrait=happy>Ah, right. They’re probably at the beach.

Text.SourceString: My hat keeps me cool.
Text.LocalizedString: My hat keeps me cool.

Text.SourceString: Is pumpkin carving still a thing around here?//I remember carving pumpkins when I was in grade school. We got to display them at the town fair.//<portrait=happy>Right, right. The Harvest Festival!
Text.LocalizedString: Is pumpkin carving still a thing around here?//I remember carving pumpkins when I was in grade school. We got to display them at the town fair.//<portrait=happy>Right, right. The Harvest Festival!

Text.SourceString: I found this green jacket in one of Mom’s chests.//Can you believe it?
Text.LocalizedString: I found this green jacket in one of Mom’s chests.//Can you believe it?

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually wear red. You see, I like to blend in with the forest.//This sweater makes me pop.//<portrait=happy>But it was free, so hey, what can I say?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually wear red. You see, I like to blend in with the forest.//This sweater makes me pop.//<portrait=happy>But it was free, so hey, what can I say?

Text.SourceString: My hat, well, it keeps me warm when the chill of Winter sets in.//Gotta make sure to stay cozy.
Text.LocalizedString: My hat, well, it keeps me warm when the chill of Winter sets in.//Gotta make sure to stay cozy.

Text.SourceString: I only have one hat.//<portrait=happy>And truth be told, it's all I need, so I see no point in hoarding more.
Text.LocalizedString: I only have one hat.//<portrait=happy>And truth be told, it's all I need, so I see no point in hoarding more.

Text.SourceString: I’ll get a new one when this one has holes in it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll get a new one when this one has holes in it.

Text.SourceString: I like spending my free time here.//<portrait=happy>These animals are my friends.
Text.LocalizedString: I like spending my free time here.//<portrait=happy>These animals are my friends.

Text.SourceString: Why don't we take a little break and chill for a bit?//I’ll put something on the TV if you want.
Text.LocalizedString: Why don't we take a little break and chill for a bit?//I’ll put something on the TV if you want.
